Subject: Oops! An Error Occurred The server returned a "500 Internal Server Error".
Description: Oops! An Error Occurred The server returned a "500 Internal Server Error". Something is broken Please e-mail us at support@endpointprotector.com and let us know what you were doing when this error occurred. We will fix it as soon as possible. Sorry for any inconvenience caused.
What_We_Know__c:
Connected remote to the clients machine along with Botond-Robert Biro to assist them further.
Client did the snapshot first then we accessed the back up.
From what we've found they had the 5th partition full so we went on an removed the old backups along with the shadows and upgrade patch backups(client agreed with all of them).
After that, about 10% of the partition was occupied and we tried to access the portal again.
He was able to get in successfully.
Next_Steps__c: Will sent a note with the recap and close the case.
Solution_Comment__c: Issue solved after removing old backups from the backend.
